<TITLE> Govt reshuffles seven joint secretaries, equivalent ranks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 1 (bdnews24.com) Seven joint secretaries and equivalently ranked officials in the administration were transferred Saturday in a ministry of establishment-ordered reshuffle. Joint secretary of the communications ministry Shafique Alam Mehedi has been made chairman of the Parjatan Corporation. Joint secretary of the agriculture ministry Munshi Alauddun Al Azad was transferred to the post of director of the military land and cantonment directorate and made joint secretary of the science, information and communication technology ministry. Shamsul Alam Khan has been appointed commissioner for refugee relief and rehabilitation at Cox's Bazar on deputation. Director of military land and cantonment directorate Faruq Ahmed has been transferred to the ministry of agriculture. Director of Bangladesh Insurance Academy Hasan Imam has been sent to the ministry of communications. Refugee relief and rehabilitation commissioner at Cox's Bazar Ahmed Hossain Khan has been transferred to the post of joint secretary in the ministry of science, information and communication technology. Additional divisional commissioner of Khulna Shamima Sultana has been given the additional role of managing director of Khulna WASA. bdnew
